Habib Bank Net Income Rises 27% on Fewer Provisions

-- B y   K h u r r u m   A n i s
-- 
2011-02-18T11:16:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-18/habib-bank-net-income-rises-27-on-fewer-provisions-update1-.html
  Habib Bank Ltd ., Pakistanâ€™s second
biggest by assets, reported a 27 percent increase in net profit
for the full year ended Dec. 31 on higher interest income and
fewer provisions for bad loans.  Net income rose to 17.03 billion rupees ($199 million), or
16.78 rupees a share, from 13.4 billion rupees, or 13.36 rupees,
in 2009, the bank said in a statement to the Karachi  Stock
Exchange  today. Revenue climbed 8 percent to 94.1 billion rupees.  The Karachi-based lender plans to pay a cash dividend of
6.5 rupees a share and to give 10 bonus shares for every 100
shares held, according to the statement.  Habib Bank fell 1.6 percent to 123 rupees as of 4:06 p.m.
local time, on course for its biggest decline since Jan. 3.  To contact the reporter on this story:
